---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.svelte";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.svelte";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FAQ — Player Data & Valuations"
  description="How Moose Sports Empire ingests baseball data and turns it into season & next-seven projections."
  noindex={false}
>
  <div class="flex min-h-screen flex-col">
    <Navbar client:load />
    <main class="flex-1">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 space-y-10">
        <div>
          <div
            class="font-mono text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner) mb-1"
          >
            Front Office FAQ
          </div>
          <h1
            class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text)"
          >
            Player Data Playbook
          </h1>
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-(--color-text-muted) mt-1">
            // HOW WE BLEND YAHOO, MLB & VEGAS SIGNALS
          </p>
        </div>

        <section>
          <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
            Moose Sports Empire is a baseball nerd&#39;s laboratory: we marry
            official Yahoo fantasy feeds with MLB tracking data, Statcast
            expected stats, and matchup intel from Vegas markets. Below is a
            transparent rundown of every source that flows into the Team Bench
            page and how it shapes the values you see.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-6">
          <h2
            class="font-display text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text)"
          >
            Data Sources We Trust
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="card p-5 space-y-3">
              <p
                class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner)"
              >
                Yahoo Fantasy Stats & Injuries
              </p>
              <h3
                class="font-display text-lg font-extrabold text-(--color-text)"
              >
                In-Season StatLine Engine
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
                Daily box scores, roster positions, and official injury tags
                come straight from Yahoo. We aggregate counting stats (R, HR,
                RBI, SB, W, SV, K, etc.) plus ratio components (AVG, ERA, WHIP)
                inside the <code
                  class="font-mono text-xs bg-(--color-surface-inset) px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-sm"
                  >stat_line</code
                > table.
              </p>
              <ul
                class="space-y-1 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5"
              >
                <li>
                  Fresh stats fuel the <strong>season</strong> z-scores once real
                  games are underway.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Injury strings (DTD, IL10, IL60, OUT) seed our injury-weight
                  multiplier.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] text-(--color-text-muted)">
                Used for: Season valuations, roster eligibility, live injury
                badges.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card p-5 space-y-3">
              <p
                class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner)"
              >
                MLB Stats API
              </p>
              <h3
                class="font-display text-lg font-extrabold text-(--color-text)"
              >
                Live Season Statistics
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
                We fetch season-to-date player statistics directly from the
                official MLB Stats API. Every player has a
                <code
                  class="font-mono text-xs bg-(--color-surface-inset) px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-sm"
                  >stat_line</code
                > record with current season performance data for daily
                z-score computations.
              </p>
              <ul
                class="space-y-1 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5"
              >
                <li>
                  Category mapping keeps Yahoo&#39;s labels aligned with MLB Stats
                  API fields.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Live stats are fetched daily and used for z-score
                  computations.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] text-(--color-text-muted)">
                Used for: Early-season stability, bench depth scouting.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card p-5 space-y-3">
              <p
                class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner)"
              >
                MLB + Statcast
              </p>
              <h3
                class="font-display text-lg font-extrabold text-(--color-text)"
              >
                Probable Starters &amp; Expected Skill
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
                We ping the MLB Stats API for the next week of games to learn
                which pitchers are lined up for one or two starts. On the skills
                side, Statcast xwOBA (hitters) and xERA (pitchers) ride
                alongside value snapshots to surface underlying quality.
              </p>
              <ul
                class="space-y-1 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5"
              >
                <li>
                  2-start SPs earn a hefty schedule multiplier in the <strong
                    >next 7</strong
                  > model.
                </li>
                <li>
                  xStats display in the Bench table so you can sniff regression
                  in or out.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] text-(--color-text-muted)">
                Used for: Next-week boosts, xStat columns.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card p-5 space-y-3">
              <p
                class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner)"
              >
                Vegas &amp; Odds APIs
              </p>
              <h3
                class="font-display text-lg font-extrabold text-(--color-text)"
              >
                Matchup Intelligence
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
                The Odds API provides implied win probabilities for every MLB
                club. We convert that into a matchup multiplier so hot favorites
                get a nudge and heavy underdogs cool off a touch.
              </p>
              <ul
                class="space-y-1 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5"
              >
                <li>Win ≥ 65% → 1.15x bump, Win ≤ 35% → 0.85x drag.</li>
                <li>
                  Applied only to <strong>next 7</strong> valuations, when schedule
                  context matters most.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] text-(--color-text-muted)">
                Used for: Matchup multipliers (GamblingService).
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card p-5 space-y-3">
              <p
                class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner)"
              >
                Yahoo Percent-Owned
              </p>
              <h3
                class="font-display text-lg font-extrabold text-(--color-text)"
              >
                Roster % &amp; Trend Pulse
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
                A nightly cron hits Yahoo&#39;s <code
                  class="font-mono text-xs bg-(--color-surface-inset) px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-sm"
                  >percent_owned</code
                > endpoint in batches of 25 players. We stamp the day&#39;s roster
                percentage onto each snapshot and compare it to the mark three days
                ago to derive the trend value shown on the Bench table.
              </p>
              <ul
                class="space-y-1 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5"
              >
                <li>
                  Positive trend = managers everywhere are adding the player.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Zero trend = stable ownership, usually veterans in secure
                  roles.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] text-(--color-text-muted)">
                Used for: Rost% column + +/- sparkline.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-6">
          <h2
            class="font-display text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text)"
          >
            How We Calculate Value
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="card p-5 space-y-3">
              <p
                class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner)"
              >
                Pipeline Overview
              </p>
              <ol
                class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed list-decimal pl-5"
              >
                <li>
                  <strong class="text-(--color-text)"
                    >Assemble player profiles.</strong
                  > We merge Yahoo stat totals with MLB Stats API live data and
                  include injury status, Yahoo rank, Statcast xStats, and
                  schedule/matchup tags.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong class="text-(--color-text)"
                    >Convert each stat to a z-score.</strong
                  > For every Yahoo category a league tracks, we compute
                  <code
                    class="font-mono text-xs bg-(--color-surface-inset) px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-sm"
                    >z = (player - mean) / stdev</code
                  >. Negative stats (ERA, WHIP) get inverted so lower is better.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong class="text-(--color-text)"
                    >Blend into a composite.</strong
                  > We take the mean of all category z-scores to form a base composite.
                  If a player has zero data sources, we lean on their Yahoo rank to
                  avoid lumping prospects at 0.00.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong class="text-(--color-text)"
                    >Adjust for context.</strong
                  >
                  <ul class="mt-1 space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
                    <li>
                      <em>Season Value:</em> composite × injury_weight (based on status).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <em>Next 7 Value:</em> (1 + composite) × injury_weight × schedule_multiplier
                      × matchup_multiplier.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong class="text-(--color-text)"
                    >Rank + store snapshots.</strong
                  > We sort composite values to assign our internal rank, pair it
                  with the latest Yahoo rank, then persist everything in <code
                    class="font-mono text-xs bg-(--color-surface-inset) px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-sm"
                    >player_value_snapshot</code
                  > for the Bench API to read.
                </li>
              </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div class="card p-5 space-y-3">
                <p
                  class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner)"
                >
                  Season Value
                </p>
                <h3
                  class="font-display text-lg font-extrabold text-(--color-text)"
                >
                  Long View, Real Stats
                </h3>
                <ul
                  class="space-y-1 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5"
                >
                  <li>Powered primarily by accumulated Yahoo stat lines.</li>
                  <li>
                    Projections only fill a category if you don&#39;t have real
                    data yet.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Injury weight table trims value: DTD=0.6, IL10=0.2,
                    IL60/OUT=0.0.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Displayed as the green/red number in the season column.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="card p-5 space-y-3">
                <p
                  class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner)"
                >
                  Next 7 Value
                </p>
                <h3
                  class="font-display text-lg font-extrabold text-(--color-text)"
                >
                  Short Burst Forecast
                </h3>
                <ul
                  class="space-y-1 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5"
                >
                  <li>
                    Starts with the same composite backbone as season value.
                  </li>
                  <li>2-start SP boost: up to 1.8× schedule multiplier.</li>
                  <li>
                    Missed games adjustment: (7 - projected DNP) ÷ 7 when we
                    know absences.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Vegas matchup multiplier to reflect soft vs. brutal weeks.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-6">
          <h2
            class="font-display text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text)"
          >
            Quick Hits &amp; Notes
          </h2>
          <div
            class="card p-5 space-y-4 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed"
          >
            <p>
              <strong class="text-(--color-text)"
                >Why can a low Yahoo rank still grade well?</strong
              > If a player is just back from the IL, our composite values spike as
              soon as their per-category z-scores climb, even before Yahoo updates
              their public rank.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong class="text-(--color-text)"
                >What if a player has no data anywhere?</strong
              > They land at a neutral 0.0 composite but still inherit our injury
              weighting and show up on the roster list so you know the slot is occupied.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong class="text-(--color-text)"
                >Why do some numbers turn yellow?</strong
              > BenchView highlights stale data when the snapshot timestamps are more
              than 24 hours old, reminding you to kick off a recompute if needed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-6">
          <h2
            class="font-display text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text)"
          >
            Glossary for Data Nerds
          </h2>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
            <div class="card p-5 space-y-2">
              <p
                class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner)"
              >
                Composite Value
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
                Average of every active category z-score after directional
                fixes. Positive = above-league-average contributor.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="card p-5 space-y-2">
              <p
                class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner)"
              >
                Injury Weight
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
                Scalar derived from Yahoo status or projected missed games.
                Multiplies straight into the composite for realism.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="card p-5 space-y-2">
              <p
                class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-(--color-commissioner)"
              >
                Roster Trend
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
                Today&#39;s percent-owned minus the mark three days prior. Spot
                emerging pickups or dead roster spots instantly.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <div
          class="mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-(--color-border-subtle) text-center"
        >
          <p
            class="font-display text-lg font-extrabold text-(--color-text) mb-1"
          >
            Still curious?
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted)">
            Ping the commish channel or open an issue — we love talking shop.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <Footer client:load />
    </main>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
